CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 17, 1962, page 23, reads: "Depicting An Era - This quartet depicted another era at the McKeesport YWCA board members' reunion last Saturday. They represented the young girls who first attended the branch-owned Camp Yo Wo Cha, near Ligonier. Wearing costumes so popular in former years, they are (from left) Mis Edith Richards, Mrs. David Rhodes, Mrs. Edward Phillips, chairman of the building fund committee, and Mrs. William Laughlin, corresponding secretary of the board. - Harris Photos"
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of four women, left to right: Edith Richards wearing t-shirt that reads "Camp Yo - Wo..." weaving basket, Mrs. Rhodes, Mrs. Phillips holding tennis racket, and Mrs. Laughlin holding baseball glove, gathered in corner of interior with windows with blinds, telephone, and bookshelf with globe for the McKeesport YWCA board members' reunion
